SIMPLE: adjudication
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adjudication
<hw>Ad*ju`di*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adjudicatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>adjudication</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of adjudicating; the act or process of trying
and determining judicially.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A deliberate determination by the judicial power; a
judicial decision or sentence.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>adjudication</xex>
in favor of natural rights.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bankruptcy practice)</fld> <def>The decision upon
the question whether the debtor is a bankrupt.</def>
<rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>A process by which land is
attached security or in satisfaction of a debt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adjudicative</ent>⟦br⟧
